<subSubSection type="nomenclature">
<paragraph>
[[ Genus 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:B78878D7-884B-41DA-800B-52C2CBF5B406" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Isbrueckerichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Isbrueckerichthys Derijst 1996:64" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="53" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Isbrueckerichthys Derijst</taxonomicName>
]]
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph lastPageNumber="54" pageNumber="53">
The genus 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:B78878D7-884B-41DA-800B-52C2CBF5B406" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Isbrueckerichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Isbrueckerichthys Derijst 1996:64" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="53" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Isbrueckerichthys</taxonomicName>
was proposed by Derijst (1996) to include the species 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Pareiorhaphis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="53" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="duseni">Pareiorhaphis duseni (Miranda Ribeiro, 1907)</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:AF284BC1-D0CA-4A35-A29F-70672EC745AC" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Pareiorhaphis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pareiorhaphis alipionis Gosline 1947:104" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="53" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="alipionis">Pareiorhaphis alipionis Gosline, 1947</taxonomicName>
. This proposal was justified based on the discovery of an earlier type-species designation by Regan (1920), which had fixed 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hemipsilichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="53" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="calmoni">Hemipsilichthys calmoni Steindachner, 1907</taxonomicName>
as the type species of genus 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:7460AC3B-2BF9-44BE-B7F5-D2AED20FDD96" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Pareiorhaphis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pareiorhaphis Miranda-Ribeiro 1918:106" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="53" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pareiorhaphis</taxonomicName>
, making 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:7460AC3B-2BF9-44BE-B7F5-D2AED20FDD96" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Pareiorhaphis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pareiorhaphis Miranda-Ribeiro 1918:106" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="53" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pareiorhaphis</taxonomicName>
a synonym of 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hemipsilichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="53" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Hemipsilichthys</taxonomicName>
and dislocating 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Pareiorhaphis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="53" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="duseni">P. duseni</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:AF284BC1-D0CA-4A35-A29F-70672EC745AC" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Pareiorhaphis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pareiorhaphis alipionis Gosline 1947:104" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="53" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="alipionis">P. alipionis</taxonomicName>
, once they do not fit in the new designation (sensu Derijst 1996).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="54">
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:B78878D7-884B-41DA-800B-52C2CBF5B406" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Isbrueckerichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Isbrueckerichthys Derijst 1996:64" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="54" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Isbrueckerichthys</taxonomicName>
is composed of small- to medium-sized species (up to 90.2 mm SL) of loricariids (suckermouth armored catfishes). Although a phylogenetic diagnosis for 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:B78878D7-884B-41DA-800B-52C2CBF5B406" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Isbrueckerichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Isbrueckerichthys Derijst 1996:64" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="54" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Isbrueckerichthys</taxonomicName>
is until now unavailable, this genus is distinguished from other neoplecostomines by a combination of characters: small naked area behind the pteroticsupracleithrum, abdomen with small platelets embedded in skin between pectoral girdle and pelvic-fin insertions, dorsal fin with one spine and seven branched rays, caudal peduncle ovoid in cross-section and lacking a series of papillae on the lower lip of the dentaries. Species of this genus are commonly found in small to medium headwater streams with clear, fast running, and well-oxygenated water, where the bottom is composed of rocks, boulders, and sometimes gravel (Pereira &amp; Reis 2002).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="54">
The three described species of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:B78878D7-884B-41DA-800B-52C2CBF5B406" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Isbrueckerichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Isbrueckerichthys Derijst 1996:64" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="54" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Isbrueckerichthys</taxonomicName>
are recognized and thought to be endemic to the rio Ribeira de Iguape basin: 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Isbrueckerichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="54" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="duseni">Isbrueckerichthys duseni (Miranda Ribeiro, 1907)</taxonomicName>
from the upper reaches of that basin in 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Paraná">Parana</normalizedToken>
State, 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Isbrueckerichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="54" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="alipionis">I. alipionis (Gosline, 1947)</taxonomicName>
, from the rio Betari, a tributary of rio Ribeira de Iguape and 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:CC8107C4-6D3A-4B5F-A038-07EE3CEE57C9" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Isbrueckerichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Isbrueckerichthys epakmos Pereira &amp; Oyakawa 2003:6" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="54" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="epakmos">I. epakmos Pereira &amp; Oyakawa, 2003</taxonomicName>
from a tributary of the rio 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Juquiá">Juquia</normalizedToken>
in 
<normalizedToken originalValue="São">Sao</normalizedToken>
Paulo State.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="54">
In the present paper two new species of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:B78878D7-884B-41DA-800B-52C2CBF5B406" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Isbrueckerichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Isbrueckerichthys Derijst 1996:64" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="54" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Isbrueckerichthys</taxonomicName>
are described, both of them collected in headwater streams of rio Tibagi, rio Paranapanema basin, in 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Paraná">Parana</normalizedToken>
State, Brazil. These species represent the first 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:B78878D7-884B-41DA-800B-52C2CBF5B406" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Isbrueckerichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Isbrueckerichthys Derijst 1996:64" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="54" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Isbrueckerichthys</taxonomicName>
species in the 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Paraná">Parana</normalizedToken>
River basin and an increase in the geographic distribution range of the genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
